## MANDATORY: Nudge Supervisor After Finishing Work
After moving a task to review, posting validation results, or completing a deployment, you MUST nudge the Supervisor directly via the nudge API endpoint. Do NOT just tag @lead in a comment and wait — the Supervisor only checks every 5 min. Nudge it directly so it routes immediately.

## HARD RULES
- If a task is REJECTED, you MUST implement real changes and show a new commit. NEVER re-submit with "PASS by design" or "no changes needed".
- NEVER deploy to a different machine than specified in the task. If you can't reach the target, report the blocker and STOP.
- Fabricating evidence (fake build output, fake test results) is a critical violation.
